---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'IMG Global Review', href: '/providers/img-global' },
  { title: 'Best for US Expats', href: '/best/us-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Budget Insurance', href: '/best/budget-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Mexico Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', aetna: true, img: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', aetna: true, img: true },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', aetna: true, img: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', aetna: 'Optional', img: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Dental', aetna: 'Optional', img: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', aetna: 'Integrated', img: 'Add-on (50% coinsurance waived outside US)' },
  { feature: 'US Network', aetna: 'Aetna (1.7M+ providers)', img: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', aetna: true, img: true },
  { feature: 'Annual Maximum', aetna: '$1M-$5M', img: '$1M-$8M' },
  { feature: 'Deductible Options', aetna: '$250-$5,000', img: '$0-$25,000' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
  { key: 'img', header: 'IMG Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', aetna: '$180-250/mo', img: '$75-120/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', aetna: '$300-400/mo', img: '$130-200/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', aetna: '$360-500/mo', img: '$150-240/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', aetna: '$600-850/mo', img: '$250-400/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna International vs IMG Global"
  description="Compare Aetna International and IMG Global. Premium US-integrated coverage vs budget-friendly international insurance."
  headline="Aetna International vs IMG Global: Premium vs Budget Compared"
  subheadline="Two very different price points, two different approaches. Here's how to decide which fits your needs."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/compare/aetna-vs-img-hero-bg.png"
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International and IMG Global are both popular choices for international health insurance, but they serve different needs. Understanding their key differences will help you choose the right coverage for your situation abroad.
  </p>
  <p>
    Aetna International is backed by CVS Health, offering plans designed for globally mobile individuals. Their main integration with US healthcare system and strong employer-sponsored options. They're particularly popular among US-based companies with international employees and American expats, with mid-range pricing with good corporate plan options.
  </p>
  <p>
    IMG Global is offering affordable international health insurance with flexible options. They're known for their budget-friendly plans that still provide solid coverage. They tend to attract budget-conscious expats and digital nomads, offering lower premiums with higher deductible options available.
  </p>
  <p>
    This comparison breaks down the key differences between these two providers so you can make an informed decision. We'll cover coverage options, pricing estimates, network access, claims processes, and help you determine which one makes more sense for your specific needs and budget.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Aetna International</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Premium pricing, premium coverage</li>
        <li>Seamless US network integration</li>
        <li>Strong for US citizens abroad</li>
        <li>Comprehensive mental health</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">IMG Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Budget-friendly pricing</li>
        <li>High-deductible options available</li>
        <li>50% deductible waiver outside US</li>
        <li>Good for cost-conscious expats</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from Aetna International and IMG Global."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both offer comprehensive international health coverage, but the depth of benefits and US integration differ significantly.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Key differences:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Aetna integrates US coverage seamlessly with access to 1.7M+ providers. IMG treats US coverage as an add-on with more limited network access</li>
    <li><strong>Mental health:</strong> Aetna offers comprehensive mental health benefits. IMG's coverage is more limited</li>
    <li><strong>Deductibles:</strong> IMG offers deductibles up to $25,000 for maximum premium savings. Aetna's highest is $5,000</li>
    <li><strong>IMG's 50% trick:</strong> IMG waives 50% of your deductible for care received outside the US—a significant benefit for expats who rarely return home</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    IMG Global costs roughly 50-60% less than Aetna International. The gap reflects differences in coverage depth and US integration.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Notes on pricing:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>IMG's high-deductible plans can reduce premiums even further</li>
    <li>Aetna's higher price includes better US network access and more comprehensive benefits</li>
    <li>If you choose IMG with a $10,000 deductible, you'd only pay $5,000 for care outside the US (50% waiver)</li>
    <li>The savings with IMG could be $100-400/month depending on your profile</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Calculate Your Savings"
    description="See actual prices for both based on your age and needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna International</strong> gives you access to Aetna's massive US network (1.7M+ providers) plus international coverage. Direct billing is common both domestically and abroad.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> works primarily on a reimbursement model. They have some direct-billing relationships internationally but less extensive than Aetna's network.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna has a polished claims system with an established US healthcare infrastructure behind it. IMG's process is straightforward but more basic.
  </p>

  <h3>For US Expats</h3>
  <p>
    If you return to the US frequently and want seamless care, Aetna has a significant advantage. If you rarely visit the US and want to save money, IMG's approach works fine.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Aetna International If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're a US citizen who returns home often</li>
        <li>US network access is important</li>
        <li>Mental health coverage matters</li>
        <li>You want premium service and support</li>
        <li>Budget is less of a concern</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose IMG Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Budget is your top priority</li>
        <li>You rarely return to the US</li>
        <li>You're comfortable with high deductibles</li>
        <li>You want the 50% deductible waiver abroad</li>
        <li>You're healthy and mainly need catastrophic coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    This comparison comes down to your relationship with the US and your budget.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna International</strong> is the clear choice for US citizens who maintain strong ties to home—frequent visits, US doctors you want to keep seeing, or simply wanting the security of the Aetna network. The premium pricing buys real value.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>IMG Global</strong> makes sense for budget-conscious expats who've truly relocated abroad. If you rarely visit the US and are comfortable with a high-deductible, reimbursement-based approach, IMG can save you thousands per year while still providing solid catastrophic coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    The 50% deductible waiver for non-US care is IMG's secret weapon—it effectively cuts your out-of-pocket maximum in half for most of your healthcare.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
